    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24/1044</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Director of the Budget</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-19">March 19,
                            1936</date>.<lb/>[Received March 20.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I enclose a copy of a proposed
                        report<note n="1" xml:id="d492fn1">Not printed.</note> by the Secretary of
                    War on H. R. 11001, a bill “To provide for the common defense by acquiring
                    commodities essential to the manufacture of supplies for the armed forces in
                    time of emergency, and for other purposes”, such commodities to be acquired (1)
                    by purchase from foreign countries by crediting to their national debts to the
                    United States arising out of the World War an amount equal to the agreed value
                    of the commodities acquired, or (2) by exchange with foreign countries of
                    agricultural commodities owned by the Federal Government, or (3) to the extent
                    that (1) and (2) are insufficient, by direct purchase.</p>
                <p>I would greatly appreciate an expression of your views with respect to this
                    proposed legislation.</p>
                <p>Please return enclosure with your reply.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>D. W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
